# EN
To run the system, you will need 3 terminals.

Terminal 1:
  sudo python3 topologia.py

Terminal 2:
  ryu-manager ryu.app.rest_qos qos_simple_switch_13.py ryu.app.rest_conf_switch

Terminal 3:
Testing with QoS:
  ./qos_script.sh 
  
Testing without QoS:
  ./no_qos_script.sh

At the end, go to the Terminal 1 and run the desired test. With one or more of the following options:
mininet> source ./real_schen.sh
mininet> source ./var_schen.sh
mininet> source ./stab_schen.sh
mininet> source ./realist_latency_evaluation.sh
mininet> source ./stable_latency_evaluation.sh

At the end of the tests, the desired outputs were stored in the "results" folder.

Part of this work was based on the tutorial on the following link: https://osrg.github.io/ryu-book/en/html/rest_qos.html

# PT_BR
Para executar o sistema, você precisará de 3 terminais.

Terminal 1:
sudo python3 topologia.py

Terminal 2:
ryu-manager ryu.app.rest_qos qos_simple_switch_13.py ryu.app.rest_conf_switch

Terminal 3:
Testando com QoS:
./qos_script.sh

Testando sem QoS:
./no_qos_script.sh

No final, vá para o Terminal 1 e execute o teste desejado com uma ou mais das seguintes opções:
mininet> source ./real_schen.sh
mininet> source ./var_schen.sh
mininet> source ./stab_schen.sh
mininet> source ./realist_latency_evaluation.sh
mininet> source ./stable_latency_evaluation.sh

No final dos testes, as saídas desejadas foram armazenadas na pasta "results".

Parte deste trabalho foi baseada no tutorial disponível no seguinte link: https://osrg.github.io/ryu-book/en/html/rest_qos.html